# Cloudflare Pages reads this file. One rule: send www to the apex.
#
# Both hostnames serve the same site, so www.kukis.nl was a byte-identical
# second copy of every page. The canonical tag already pointed search engines
# at the apex, but a canonical is a hint — a 301 is the answer, and it also
# means links and shares land on one hostname instead of splitting.
#
# 301, not 302: this is permanent, and only a permanent redirect passes on the
# ranking signal from any links that point at www.
#
# The splat keeps the path: www.kukis.nl/anything -> kukis.nl/anything. It must
# stay a hostname-scoped rule — a bare /* would match every request on the apex
# too and redirect the site to itself forever.
https://www.kukis.nl/* https://kukis.nl/:splat 301
